"Time is of the essence. The admission and treatment work is urgent. We must Split Second and spare no effort to treat the patients. " Recently, the central government's Hubei Guiding Group has issued a series of instructions on the prevention and treatment of the new pneumonia.

However, the reporter learned that Wuhan's communities and hospitals are still overloaded, many patients who can not be treated in time are forced to be isolated at home, and relatives who are caring for them have been infected.

How to control cross-infection in the family? How to ensure the implementation of "receivable collection" ? The problem is imminent.

All four members of the family were infected, and the mother became seriously ill at the shelter hospital

Over the past few days, the central government has repeatedly stressed that the implementation of the "four categories of personnel" centralized management measures, "should be collected, do not miss a person. "Four categories of people" , including confirmed patients, suspected patients, can not rule out the possibility of infection in patients with fever, confirmed patients with close contacts. But in the face of a severe shortage of medical resources, most of the attention is focused on critically ill patients. Citizens classified as other types had to wait, and some were even dragged from close contact to infection.

Joseph Li Shan's mother, who was in her 60s and recently diagnosed with the infection, couldn't find a hospital bed. After a lot of feedback, Joseph Li Shan finally sent his mother to a shelter hospital at the Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center. However, 9 noon on the phone, his mother told him that his situation is not good.

"She was admitted to the Shelter Hospital on the 6th and has now changed from a mild case to a severe case, presenting with dyspnea. The shelter had no treatment facilities and was understaffed. The doctor could only take his temperature and give him some anti-inflammatory medicine every day. It's like moving to a different place,"Joseph Li Shan told reporters.

Joseph Li Shan's family of six, the mother first symptoms, followed by the father. But when the couple went to the hospital, the hospital refused to examine Joseph Li Shan's father. "The doctor told my father to wait a week, but two days later my father felt something was wrong and went to the hospital to do it again, " he said. After reporting the case to the community, he was placed in isolation at Wuhan Women's Hospital. But there, like a hotel, was "room and board only, " and my father had not yet received any treatment.

To make matters worse, after days on the road, Joseph Li Shan has been diagnosed with a new case of pneumonia, and her lover is highly suspected. The two men were diagnosed in a similar way to their father, after several failed hospital visits and only recently getting tested in the community.

"I wanted to report it to the Wuhan First Hospital and told the doctor that both my parents were infected, but the doctor said I couldn't do it because the symptoms were not serious, and only had blood tests and a CT scan done. Samples were taken at the Community Hospital on the afternoon of February 7. I was diagnosed with infection on February 8. My wife needs to be watched."

On Feb. 8, Joseph Li Shan turned to the community and was told to go home and wait. At 8 p.m. , the community arranged for Joseph Li Shan to be hospitalized and his family to be quarantined. But Joseph Li Shan waited until after 8:00 and was told he couldn't make the arrangements for the day and would have to wait at home.

Joseph Li Shan and her partner are still at home, with two children, eight years old and four months old. While the child is asymptomatic, Joseph Li Shan worries that it is only a matter of time before the child becomes infected. In addition to eating, the family wears masks at home all day, including when they sleep. Does the hospital take children now? Do I need to go to a children's hospital? Will go to the hospital infection risk is bigger? These days, Joseph Li Shan struggles every day.

"It is hoped that the government will be able to equip the shelter hospital with the necessary equipment, medicines and manpower so that its patients can be treated as soon as possible and that the seriously ill patients can be transferred to regular hospitals as soon as possible. Now many people can not be diagnosed or can not be treated, repeatedly to the hospital is also very dangerous, easy to cause the spread of disease. People like us who are diagnosed are actually afraid of infecting more people,"Joseph Li Shan said.

Suspected patients are difficult to be diagnosed and admitted to treatment, home infection cases emerge one after another

Worryingly, there are many more families like Joseph Li Shan's in Wuhan. A family in home quarantine in a series of discomfort, repeatedly contacted the hospital was told that there is no bed, can not be hospitalized only in the outpatient line five or six hours injection... their daily life, it's a long, drawn-out ordeal.

Wang Li, a 22-year-old recent college graduate from Wuhan, lives in Jiang'an District. On January 26, her father was sent to the No. 2 Hospital of Wuhan Iron and steel for isolation because of a high suspicion of new crown pneumonia.

Shortly after, the mother, who was a close contact, also developed pneumonia, and a CT scan at a sentinel hospital showed "double lung infection. ". Wang immediately reported the situation to the community, the community to the mother arranged nucleic acid testing. But the community asked Wang Li's mother to go to the quarantine point first, on the grounds that her mother was suffering from a fever. In desperation, Wang Li sent her mother to a designated isolation point near the citizens'home on Jiang'an District's back Lake Avenue.

Subsequently, Wang Li again contact the community street office request nucleic acid testing, the other side said there is a unified arrangement, to see what the person in charge of the isolation point. Wang Li contacts quarantine point instead, get only"I understand, will report as soon as possible"reply. In this way, Wang Li fell into the isolation point and the street office mutual escape dilemma.

NO NUCLEIC ACID test, no diagnosis, means that the mother can not be timely treatment. "there was no oxygen machine and no way to give fluids at the isolation point where my mother was, " Wang said. "She was alone in the hotel and told me she was afraid. She wanted to get an injection. She felt bad. She wanted to live. ".

On the other side, Wang Li's father could not wait for timely treatment. She told reporters that her father went into shock on July 7 and was later transferred to Wuhan Union Hospital, where doctors diagnosed pneumonia as a cause of myocarditis and cerebral embolism. Just yesterday morning, Wang Li, 47, lost her father.

Wang Li's father is in the hospital.

On the evening of the 8th, Wang Li went to Hankou Hospital for a CT scan and also found a mild infection. But now, instead of confirming her condition, she was hoping that her mother would be diagnosed and treated sooner.

Similar to Wang, Yu Ting, who lives in Hanyang District, has not been able to get help from her family and is now feeling unwell.

Yu Ting recalled that her father had already taken a CT scan in late January showing "double lung infection" , and the family immediately contacted the community for nucleic acid testing. However, contact the community for six days in a row, were "we can only report, can not solve" the answer. While she waited, she had to take her father to a nearby hospital for an injection to reduce inflammation. She watched as his illness turned from mild to severe, but she couldn't find a hospital to admit him.

More to Yu Ting worry is that after his father may not even injection place. "clinics in some of the surrounding hospitals have been closed. My father got an injection at the Hanyang Hospital recommended by the community, and after six days of no improvement, he went to the Qiao estuary lung hospital for four days. If my father's disease goes untreated, maybe I can't control myself,"she said.
Yu Ting accompanied her father to the lung hospital shot photos.

These endless cases reflect the current embarrassing situation in Wuhan: Citizens can only do CT examinations in hospitals and nucleic acid tests in the community to be diagnosed; the community is seriously understaffed and has limited powers, it is not possible to arrange nucleic acid testing in a timely manner for the general public; while waiting for confirmation, the family members of the patients, as close contacts, have also developed infections or even whole families; they are unable to receive diagnosis and treatment, repeated visits to community or hospital clinics only exacerbate the risk of the spread of the epidemic.

There's no treatment at the isolation point, and the patient can't self-medicate

Reporters noted that the important requirements of the implementation of "four categories of personnel" classification centralized management measures, many suspected patients, fever patients were centralized to the isolation point. Due to the tense situation of the epidemic, the quarantine point can only be temporarily resettled patients, further processing, reporting and sending medical work only recently slowly on the right track.

Ho Ran and his family lived in Caidian District. His wife developed a cough and fever on New Year's Eve. The next day he checked in with the community and isolated himself. During the consultation, his wife's symptoms gradually aggravated, he ran heard that playing globulin useful, he asked a friend to buy a few. They had intended to be in the fever clinic after prescribing medicine to the community hospital injection, found that the community can not play, only to the designated hospital fever clinic. "there were so many people, they had to wait hours for a shot. "

On February 2, Mrs. He ran was in the hospital receiving injection, suddenly received the community's unified quarantine notice. "We were in a hurry, so we simply packed up and drove to our designated spot just after 11:00 and didn't know who to call. Then I ran into a patient, gave him his name, and he took my wife to the fourth floor. It was probably an emergency place, and on the way up, I saw someone cleaning up. It was 1:00 in the morning when my wife got her room. She said she saw blood in the sink and didn't dare to use it, but she stayed there first."He ran said.

However, like Joseph Li Shan and Wang Li's family, she did not receive effective treatment at the isolation point, only medical staff came to check her temperature or ask about her condition. On the afternoon of the 3rd, the doctor opened a box of Lianhua Qingwen capsule to her and gave her a nucleic acid test. His wife wanted to continue to play the outpatient doctor's medicine, but was told not to play take-away medicine.

"We have been taking medicine for more than 10 days, from single lung infection to double lung infection, still can not prove that taking medicine does not work? The symptoms had improved with injections and Globulin supplementation, so I thought I'd keep on with the injections. Why not allow injection, and then go to eat what Lianhua qingwen capsule?"He ran was very worried, i'm afraid my wife's illness will come back. He reached out to the community and asked for help coordinating the arrangements, but that didn't work either.

Fortunately, the day after the nucleic acid test at the isolation point, Mrs. He was diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia and was admitted to the hospital that night. He Ran said that his wife's condition has improved, has no symptoms of dyspnea.

In accompany the wife to visit these days, he ran also appeared cough and fever symptoms. He suspected he had it, too, but the CT showed no "ground-glass" shadow, and the doctor said it was just inflammation. After registering with the community, he moved into another quarantine facility on February 5. The quarantine site has so far received close contacts from more than 30 confirmed patients.

The quarantine point where he ran was.

According to He ran's observation, the isolation point is the main basis for judging the condition of the body temperature, only abnormal body temperature may be sent to the hospital. Others, he found, had been quarantined at home for more than a dozen days, and had been quarantined here for only a day or two, for a total of more than 14 days.

The material that Ho ran received at the quarantine point.

At present he ran's condition is quite stable, still take the medicine that was prescribed from the Union Medical College Hospital before, if the medicine is finished, you can report to the personnel of the isolation point, they will send him to the hospital to prescribe medicine. "When we first came in, there were a lot of complaints from people who were quarantined here, and the staff were very busy. After a few days, they all got used to it. Compared to those who haven't been admitted yet, we are so happy! "

On February 7th he went to Concorde Hospital for a nucleic acid test, the results of which were not yet available.

Joseph Li Shan, Wang Li, Yu Ting, he ran

Fortunately, the day after the nucleic acid test at the isolation point, Mrs. He was diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia and was admitted to the hospital that night. He Ran said that his wife's condition has improved, has no symptoms of dyspnea.

In accompany the wife to visit these days, he ran also appeared cough and fever symptoms. He suspected he had it, too, but the CT showed no "ground-glass" shadow, and the doctor said it was just inflammation. After registering with the community, he moved into another quarantine facility on February 5. The quarantine site has so far received close contacts from more than 30 confirmed patients.

The quarantine point where he ran was.

According to He ran's observation, the isolation point is the main basis for judging the condition of the body temperature, only abnormal body temperature may be sent to the hospital. Others, he found, had been quarantined at home for more than a dozen days, and had been quarantined here for only a day or two, for a total of more than 14 days.

The material that Ho ran received at the quarantine point.

At present he ran's condition is quite stable, still take the medicine that was prescribed from the Union Medical College Hospital before, if the medicine is finished, you can report to the personnel of the isolation point, they will send him to the hospital to prescribe medicine. "When we first came in, there were a lot of complaints from people who were quarantined here, and the staff were very busy. After a few days, they all got used to it. Compared to those who haven't been admitted yet, we are so happy! "

On February 7th he went to Concorde Hospital for a nucleic acid test, the results of which were not yet available.
